ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Date script was run
time script was started
assigned subject id number
Identifier of Testing Session
Time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
The platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
Whether script was completed
Notes: 0 = Script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 1 = Script was completed (all conditions run)

ElementDescription: 6-hour delay ''indifference point''; The proportion of the maximum ($100) reward that, if presented immediately, was equal in subjective value to the maximum ($100) reward if the subject had to wait 6 h to receive the maximum.

1-day delay ''indifference point''; The proportion of the maximum ($100) reward that, if presented immediately, was equal in subjective value to the maximum ($100) reward if the subject had to wait one day to receive the maximum.

1-week delay ''indifference point''; The proportion of the maximum ($100) reward that, if presented immediately, was equal in subjective value to the maximum ($100) reward if the subject had to wait 1 week to receive the maximum.

1 month delay ''indifference point''; The proportion of the maximum ($100) reward that, if presented immediately, was equal in subjective value to the maximum ($100) reward if the subject had to wait one month to receive the maximum.

3 month delay ''indifference point''; The proportion of the maximum ($100) reward that, if presented immediately, was equal in subjective value to the maximum ($100) reward if the subject had to wait three months to receive the maximum.

1 year delay ''indifference point''; The proportion of the maximum ($100) reward that, if presented immediately, was equal in subjective value to the maximum ($100) reward if the subject had to wait one year to receive the maximum.

5-year delay ''indifference point''; The proportion of the maximum ($100) reward that, if presented immediately, was equal in subjective value to the maximum ($100) reward if the subject had to wait five years to receive the maximum.
Mean reaction time (in ms) of all choices
Median reaction time (in ms) of all choices
meanRT_immedChoices: mean latency (in ms) of ''immediate'' choices
medianRT_immedChoices: median latency (in ms) of ''immediate'' choices
meanRT_delayedChoices: mean latency (in ms) of ''delayed'' choices
medianRT_delayedChoices: median latency (in ms) of ''delayed'' choices
